This paper deals with fair division, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of a recommender system, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The modifications made to the standard CEEI algorithm involve optimizing for equity, which is a topic in economics (cs.EC). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of these modifications on the outcomes of the market, which falls under the category of computational social science (cs.CY).
